==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Triturate
<hw>Trit"u*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Triturated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Triturating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>trituratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>triturate</ets> to thrash (grain),
fr. <ets>terere</ets>, <ets>tritum</ets>, to rub, rub to pieces. See
<er>Trite</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To rub, grind, bruise, or
thrash.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To rub or grind to a very fine or impalpable powder;
to pulverize and comminute thoroughly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trituration</ent>⟦br⟧
